			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hiya, everyone.
<br />

<br />
As Feroce, an officer and wannabe tank of Molto Espressivo, the All-Bard Guild on Firiona Vie, I've had some fun times in the last year and a half.  My play time is way down these days, as I'm getting married and going into the Army, but just for kicks, I started a mage earlier today.  I've had this idea kicking around for about 8 months or so about starting an all-pet class guild.  The cheif requirement, of course, would be the ability to summon and control a pet.  
<br />

<br />
The cheif aim of this guild, at least at first, would be to explore and enjoy the possibilities of all-pet class groups, and to help out ones fellow pet masters.  Down the road, who knows?  All-pet-class raids could be fun, if a bit laggy, and if that turns out not to work so well, the
<br />

<br />
I got this idea while I was grinding through the 50's as a bard.  I noticed in one group I was leading that when I had 5 pet classes with me, we could take down relatively difficult content pretty effectively and quickly.  I also enjoyed that I could take the time to chat and get to know my group whilst the pets wailed away on our enemies.  I know that pet push could be a little problematic, but with enough mutual support and guidance, I'm sure that it, like aggro, could be handled.
<br />

<br />
This is purely a feeler-post.  Please post any relevant commentary, queries about how the all-bard guild works, guild name suggestions, class limitations (Who should be included or excluded), what a good ruleset would be, what server would be best suited for this, whatever.
<br />

<br />
Possible names (Off the top of my head, I'm sure you can come up with better)
<br />
Kennel Keepers
<br />
Pet Pride Parade
<br />
Slave Masters
<br />
Dominion of Mastery
<br />

<br />
I had fun playing my little mage today.  Just got my first elemental when I had to log.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=601903">Feroce</a> <br> 
<br />
Battle Bard, Grandmaster Smith, and Tradeskill Officer of Molto Espressivo
<br />

<br />
Gadric, Pewee Mage of Stromm</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
