<br />
I've done RS with only two other mages.  It would be very cake to chain pet RS with a full group and if you get an add well you aren't pulling correctly.
<br />

<br />

<br />
As for a guild of all pet classes, well I don't think it would work in practice.  Sure you could take out tons of targets but farming a zone to equip an unbalanced guild could become tedious to say the least.  In addition there are combinations of players that just give you the most efficient raiding experience.  Through testing everywhere, this seems to be 5 wars, 10-15+ clerics, 5 offtankers, and a buncha dps wether it is caster or melee.  And of course enough of each type to keep everyone buffed and healed.  My numbers could be off but you get the idea.  
<br />

<br />
I would love to go take out Reparm with 10-20 mages (he doesn't rampage and can only slaughter one pet per round) but this is more a one-time deal than a playstyle I would practice every day.
<br />

<br />
What I would really like to see is a mage channel that all mages autojoined and did stuff together several times a week.  Other classes welcome of course but mainly mage-bassed.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=805629" target="_blank" class="postlink">Arch Mage Magusmaximus Burninator</a>
