			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, how about some more practical questions for the people who are interested:
<br />

<br />
Which server would you want to do this on?  My immediate preferences would be Firiona Vie or Stromm.  Both have a lower jerk index, and are less crowded than most other servers.
<br />

<br />
Firiona Vie has the advantage of having next to no NO-DROP items, so a strict hand-me-down system can help to ease the problems of having to camp the same stuff over and over.  It has the disadvantage of allowing only one toon per account, however, and it's a fairly established server, with plenty of raiding guilds who'd just love to snap up new members as they get into the raiding levels.  There are also some hassles unique to Firiona Vie, such as not being allowed to bind anywhere that melee toons can't, and having no common tongue or ooc channel.  The economy there is pretty wierd, too.  Lower-end and middle-range gear is pretty cheap, but the nice stuff is VERY expensive.  
<br />

<br />
Stromm is young and hasn't yet been overrun by uber guilds.  A PVP server might be interesting, but I think most blue folks wouldn't care for the kind of hostility and frustration that they bring.  Of course, there is the issue of there being NO-DROP items there, and that could get in the way of loot, but there are ways to get around that that we did in Molto (partnering up with other guilds to raid stuff, or raiding with invited friends).  
<br />

<br />
Secondly, what counts as a pet class?  
<br />
The hard core purists would probably say Mages, Necros, and Beastlords. The classes that heavily depend upon their pets, and have a range of spells and abilities specifically tailored to use on pets. 
<br />

<br />
Those who are a bit more open to weaker pets could include hammer-bossing clerics, SK's, enchanters, shaman, and druids.  These are classes that often use pets, but don't depend on them for their basic class functionality.
<br />

<br />
Then there are classes I would consider a stretch.  Wizard pets are decorations; they can't actually be bossed about or attack anything (can they?), but if you consider the little buff decoration a real pet, I'd love to read the justification.  I probably wouldn't count any pet proccing weapon; there's no control of the pet, and it lasts only a few seconds.  Bards can charm mobs, but only for short durations, and have no pet hold or pet-specific AAs.  
<br />

<br />
If someone was desperate enough to get in, they might try doing the Gnoll Slayer quest a LOT.  That would take tons of sidework, but if someone wanted to try that hard... well, we could wind up doing what Molto did, and allow friends and alts in channel, but not in-guild.  (Molto ultimately started another guild for friends and alts).
<br />

<br />
Third, what kinds of rules would you need for such a guild?
<br />

<br />
Most guilds I've seen have pretty similar spirits behind their rules.  In Molto, we had 4 rules:
<br />

<br />
1.  No E-Bay or RL cash for anything in-game.
<br />
2.  Bards only, no other classes allowed (this would be changed to pet classes)
<br />
3.  Don't sell any gear that you can pass down.
<br />
4.  Don't be a dick.
<br />

<br />
Rules 2 and 3 were the only ones that really stood out from most other guilds or raiding alliances.  The passing down is REALLY important to Molto.  This allows peopl to get gear upgrades even if they don't win loot rolls very much.  Of course, such a rule works better on the FV server than on most regular ones.
<br />

<br />
I put the poll up more to get a head count of interest, and I like the interest I see.  I would LOVE to see such an organization take off.
<br />

<br />
By the way, if you want to laugh at my pathetic mage skills, I got my pewee mage to level 9 today on Stromm.  Having played two bards for a combined total of 111 levels, it's a lot of fun having a pet that I don't have to worry about biting me in the butt at any given moment when charm breaks.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=601903">Feroce</a> <br> 
<br />
Battle Bard, Grandmaster Smith, and Tradeskill Officer of Molto Espressivo
<br />

<br />
Gadric, Pewee Mage of Stromm</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
